{"title_page": "Hello, Love, Goodbye", "text_new": "{{short description|Filipino romantic drama film}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Hello, Love, Goodbye\n| image          = Hello-love-goodbye-poster.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Cathy Garcia-Molina]]\n| producer       = {{ubl|[[Carlo L. Katigbak]]|[[Olivia M. Lamasan]]}}\n| screenplay     = {{Plainlist|\n* Carmi G. Raymundo\n* Rona Co\n* Cathy Garcia-Molina\n|story          = Carmi G. Raymundo\n}}\n| starring       = {{ubl|[[Kathryn Bernardo]]|[[Alden Richards]]}}\n| music          = Jessie Q. Lasaten\n| cinematography = Noel Teehankee\n| editing        = Marya Ignacio\n| studio         = [[Star Cinema]]\n| distributor    = Star Cinema\n| released       = {{Film date|2019|07|31|Philippines|2019|08|09|United States|2019|08|08|Middle East}}\n| runtime        = 118 minutes\n| country        = Philippines\n| language       = Filipino\n| gross          = {{Philippine Peso|880.6 million}} ({{USD|17.3 million}})\n}}\n\n'''''Hello, Love, Goodbye''''' is a [[List of Philippine films of 2019|2019]] Philippine [[romantic drama]] film directed by [[Cathy Garcia-Molina]] and produced by [[Star Cinema]]. The film follows Joy Fabregas ([[Kathryn Bernardo]]), a struggling [[Overseas Filipino Worker|overseas Filipino worker]], and Ethan Del Rosario ([[Alden Richards]]), a bartender, as they attempt to reconcile their personal careers and love for each other in Hong Kong. Released on July 31, 2019 in the Philippines, the film is the [[list of highest-grossing Philippine films|highest grossing Philippine film]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rappler.com/entertainment/news/238450-hello-love-goodbye-earnings-box-office-worldwide-august-23-2019|title='Hello, Love, Goodbye' makes over P800 million worldwide|last=Rappler.com|website=Rappler|language=en|access-date=2019-08-28}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://entertainment.inquirer.net/344150/hello-love-goodbye-is-highest-grossing-ph-film|title=\u2018Hello, Love, Goodbye\u2019 is highest-grossing PH film|last=Hallare|first=Katrina|website=entertainment.inquirer.net|language=en|access-date=2019-09-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/amp/news/hello-love-goodbye-sets-record-at-philippines-box-office-1238526|title=\u2018Hello, Love, Goodbye\u2019 Sets Record at Philippines Box Office|website=www.hollywoodreporter.com|access-date=2019-09-10}}</ref>\n\n== Synopsis ==\nJoy ([[Kathryn Bernardo]]) is a spunky, poor millennial who works as a domestic helper in Hong Kong. While she excels in her job and enjoys the friendship of many other empowered domestic helpers, she plans to leave the city soon.\n\nIn her journey to achieving her goals, Joy meets Filipino bartender Ethan ([[Alden Richards]]). Ethan is a sweetheart playboy already building a permanent life in Hong Kong. In a few years, he will officially become a resident in the city. After escaping responsibilities all his life, Ethan now wants to commit to a career and to his family (who also reside in Hong Kong). Joy and Ethan soon develop a friendship. The two become each other's joy against the grime and grind of Hong Kong.<ref>https://emea.kapamilya.com/events/europe/hello-love-goodbye</ref>\n\n== Cast ==\n=== Main ===\n{{multiple image\n|direction = vertical\n|align = right\n|image1 = Kathryn Bernardo at the Celebrate Mega in Iceland, 2016.jpg\n|caption1 = [[Kathryn Bernardo]] portrays Joy\n|width1 = 150\n|image2 = Alden Richards at the OMG Awards.jpg\n|caption2 = [[Alden Richards]] portrays Ethan\n|width2 = 150\n}}\n* [[Kathryn Bernardo]] as Joy Marie Fabregas: <br /> A nursing graduate who works as a domestic helper in Hong Kong.<ref name=\"scout\">{{cite news |last1=Barrientos |first1=Giselle |title=In \u2018Hello, Love, Goodbye,\u2019 an OFW gets a chance to choose herself |url=https://www.scoutmag.ph/entertainment/tv-movie/hello-love-goodbye-review-giselleb-20190802 |accessdate=September 8, 2019 |work=Scout Magazine |date=August 2, 2019}}</ref> \n* [[Alden Richards]] as Ethan Del Rosario: <br/> A womanizer bartender who is on his way of attaining [[Hong Kong residency]] status who is relatively well off compared to Fabregas.<ref name=\"scout\"/>\n\n=== Supporting ===\n* [[Maymay Entrata]] as Mary Dale Fabregas\n* [[Jameson Blake]] as Edward Del Rosario\n* [[Kakai Bautista]] as Sally Daraga\n* [[Lito Pimentel]] as Mario Del Rosario\n* [[Lovely Abella]] as Gina Marikit\n* William Lorenzo as Celso Fabregas\n* Anthony Jennings as Eric Del Rosario\n* Wilbert Ross as Joey Fabregas\n* Aliyah Billote as Liezel Fabregas\n* Angela Poliquit as Annie\n* Jon Go as Wayne\n* Poon Po Lun Lilac as Lin (Annie's mother)\n\n=== Special Participation ===\n* [[Maricel Laxa]] as Lita\n* [[Maxine Medina]] as Tanya\n* [[Jerome Ponce]] as JM\n\n==Production==\nThe film is starred by [[Kathryn Bernardo]] and [[Alden Richards]] who are affiliated with the two major rival networks in the Philippines; Bernardo with [[ABS-CBN (TV network)|ABS-CBN]] and Richards with [[GMA Network]]. The two also belongs to two different \"[[love team]]s\", Bernardo who is collectively known as Kathniel with [[Daniel Padilla]] and Richards with [[Maine Mendoza]] in [[AlDub]]. Together they play two Overseas Filipino Workers in Hong Kong who became romantically involved with each other.<ref name=gulfcrossover>{{cite news |last1=Belleza |first1=Irish Eden |title=Kathryn Bernardo and Alden Richards crossover for love |url=https://gulfnews.com/entertainment/pinoy-celebs/kathryn-bernardo-and-alden-richards-crossover-for-love-1.65625011 |accessdate=September 8, 2019 |work=Gulf News |date=August 4, 2019}}</ref> Directory Cathy Garcia-Molina said that the two main cast members were not subjected to \"baby or special treatment\" for the film project.<ref name=\"served\">{{cite news |title=Kathryn Bernardo served co-workers on \u2018Hello, Love, Goodbye\u2019 movie set in HK |url=https://filipinotimes.net/entertainment/2019/06/24/kathryn-bernardo-served-co-workers-hello-love-goodbye-movie-set-hk/ |accessdate=September 8, 2019 |work=The Filipino Times |date=June 24, 2019 |language=English, Filipino}}</ref>\n\nFilming for ''Hello, Love, Goodbye'' in Hong Kong has began by April 2019<ref>{{cite news |last1=Salonga |first1=Rita |title=Kathryn, Alden start shooting in Hong Kong |url=http://dzrhnews.com.ph/kathryn-alden-start-shooting-in-hong-kong/ |accessdate=September 8, 2019 |work=DZRH News |date=April 9, 2019}}</ref> and was completed after a month<ref>{{cite news |last1=Aguilar |first1=Krissy |title=\u2018Hello, Love, Goodbye\u2019 shoot a \u2018big adjustment\u2019 for Kathryn, Daniel |url=https://entertainment.inquirer.net/337733/hello-love-goodbye-shoot-a-big-adjustment-for-kathryn-daniel |accessdate=September 8, 2019 |work=Philippine Daily Inquirer |date=July 10, 2019}}</ref> [[Principal photography]] for the film ended by May 19, 2019 in [[Sucat]], [[Para\u00f1aque]].<ref name=\"pep1\">{{cite news |title=Kathryn Bernardo-Alden Richards movie, kakatapos lang ng principal photography |trans-title=Principal photography for Kathryn Bernardo-Alden Richards movie just finishd|url=https://www.pep.ph/pepalerts/pep-troika/143382/kathryn-bernardo-alden-richards-movie-kakatapos-lang-ng-principal-photography-a4118-20190519 |accessdate=September 8, 2019 |work=PEP.ph |publisher=Philippine Entertainment Portal, Inc. |date=May 19, 2019|language=Tagalog, English}}</ref> Post-production work for ''Hello, Love, Goodbye'' was done in Bangkok, Thailand with [[ABS-CBN Film Productions]] collaborating with Thai production firm [[Kantana Group]]. It was the first collaboration between the two firms.<ref name=\"pep2\">{{cite news |last1=Anarcon |first1=James Patrick |title=Hello Love Goodbye director on Kathryn Bernardo: \"Medyo inalila talaga namin siya sa Hong Kong.\"|trans-title=Hello Love Goodbye director on Kathryn Bernardo: \"We maltreated her a bit in Hong Kong\" |url=https://www.pep.ph/guide/movies/144103/hello-love-goodbye-director-on-kathryn-bernardo-medyo-inalila-talaga-namin-siya-sa-hong-kong-a724-20190623 |accessdate=September 8, 2019 |work=PEP.ph |publisher=Philippine Entertainment Portal, Inc. |date=June 22, 2019|language=English, Filipino}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\n===Marketing===\nA [[teaser trailer|teaser]] for ''Hello, Love, Goodbye'' was released on June 14, 2019<ref>{{cite news |title=Teaser for Kathryn Bernardo, Alden Richards movie 'Hello, Love, Goodbye' released |url=https://www.rappler.com/entertainment/movies/233086-hello-love-goodbye-teaser-trailer |accessdate=September 8, 2019 |work=Rappler |date=June 14, 2019}}</ref> while the official full trailer for  was released by Star Cinema on July 1, 2019.<ref name=posters>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cosmo.ph/entertainment/international-posters-kathryn-bernardo-alden-richards-film-hello-love-goodbye-a434-20190707|title=The International Posters For Kathryn Bernardo + Alden Richards' Film 'Hello, Love, Goodbye' Will Make You Kilig|last=Shi|first=Stephanie|date=July 7, 2019|work=Cosmopolitan|access-date=September 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Theatrical run===\n''Hello, Love, Goodbye'' premiered in the Philippines on July 31, 2019<ref name=posters/> in 465 cinemas, a record.{{Citation needed|date=September 2019}} The international screenings started on August 1, 2019.{{Citation needed|date=September 2019}} The film also made history in Saudi Arabia as the first Filipino film ever to be screened in the cinemas of Jeddah.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/08/06/19/hello-love-goodbye-is-first-ph-film-to-be-shown-in-jeddah-saudi|title='Hello, Love, Goodbye' is first PH film to be shown in Jeddah, Saudi Arabia|last=News|first=ABS-CBN|website=ABS-CBN News|access-date=2019-08-14}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Box office===\nThe film was declared the highest-grossing film of all time after earning over {{Philippine Peso|880 million}} worldwide gross revenue on September 3, 2019, replacing the film ''[[The Hows of Us]]'' that was also directed by Molina and starred by Bernardo.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/09/03/19/hello-love-goodbye-makes-history-as-highest-grossing-ph-film-of-all-time|title='Hello, Love, Goodbye' makes history as highest grossing PH film of all time|website=ABS-CBN News|access-date=2019-09-04}}</ref>\n\n====Domestic====\nThe film on its opening day earned a total of {{Philippine Peso|34.4 million}} from over 350 cinemas in the Philippines.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/08/01/19/hello-love-goodbye-earns-p34-million-on-opening-day|title='Hello, Love, Goodbye' earns P34 million on opening day|date=1 August 2019|work=ABA-CBN News|access-date=}}</ref> Three days after its local release, the film was reported to have earned {{Philippine Peso|110.8 million}}.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/08/03/19/hello-love-goodbye-collects-p110-million-in-3-days|title='Hello, Love, Goodbye' collects P110 million in 3 days|date=1 August 2019|work=ABS-CBN News|access-date=}}</ref> After four days, the film earned {{Philippine Peso|176.6 million}}<ref name=\":1\" /> and was shown in 465 cinemas nationwide.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/08/05/19/hello-love-goobye-earns-p250m-in-less-than-a-week|title='Hello, Love, Goobye' earns P250M in less than a week|date=5 August 2019|work=ABS-CBN News|access-date=}}</ref> As of August 12, 2019, the film has grossed {{Philippine Peso|505.7 million}} domestically in 13 days of showing.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://starcinema.abs-cbn.com/2019/8/12/news/hello-love-goodbye-hits-500m-in-local-box-off-51709|title=\u2018Hello, Love, Goodbye\u2019 hits \u20b1500M in local box office! {{!}} Star Cinema|last=Maglaqui|first=Rhovin|website=starcinema.abs-cbn.com|language=en|access-date=2019-08-20}}</ref> After 17 days in cinemas, the film has grossed {{Philippine Peso|603 million}} domestically.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/08/17/19/hello-love-goodbye-racks-up-p600-million|title='Hello, Love, Goodbye' racks up P600 million|publisher=ABS-CBN News|date=17 August 2019|access-date=17 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n====International====\nThe film earned {{USD|2,132,000.00}} in box office receipts abroad on its first week of release.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/08/17/19/hello-love-goodbye-racks-up-p600-million|title='Hello, Love, Goodbye' racks up P600 million|website=ABS-CBN News||date=|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=2019-08-20}}</ref> The film was also recognized now the highest-grossing Filipino film in the Middle East for earning over {{USD|1 million}} as of August 18.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abs-cbn.com/newsroom/news-releases/hello-love-goodbye-marks-box-office-record-in?lang=en|title=\"Hello, Love, Goodbye\" marks box-office record in the Middle East {{!}} ABS-CBN Corporate|website=ABS-CBN Corporation|access-date=2019-08-22}}</ref> It is also the highest-grossing Filipino film in Australia, New Zealand and United Kingdom earning over {{USD|195,336.00}},<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.the-numbers.com/movie/Hello-Love-Goodbye-(Philippines)/Australia|title=Hello, Love, Goodbye - Financial Information Australia|website=The Numbers|access-date=2019-09-10}}</ref> {{USD|60,459.00}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/intl/?page=&country=NZ&wk=2019W32&id=_fHELLOLOVEGOODB01|title=Hello, Love, Goodbye|website=www.boxofficemojo.com|access-date=2019-08-27}}</ref> and {{USD|32,313.00}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/intl/?page=&country=UK&wk=2019W32&id=_fHELLOLOVEGOODB01|title=Hello, Love, Goodbye|website=www.boxofficemojo.com|access-date=2019-09-03}}</ref> respectively.\n\n===Critical response===\nFilipino film critic Philbert Dy gave the film a rating of 4 out of 5 and praised Bernardo's performance.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://letterboxd.com/faithlessphil/film/hello-love-goodbye/|title='Hello, Love, Goodbye' Review by Philbert Dy |last=|first=|date=|work=|access-date=}}</ref> Oggs Cruz, writing for [[Rappler]], reviewed the film thus, \"Hello, Love, Goodbye' is fine entertainment \u2013 one that doesn\u2019t dumb down the issues it puts forward for the sake of a standard happy ending.\" He pointed out that while the romantic plot was formulaic and characters seemed to have become stereotypical, the film's strengths were its depiction of Hong Kong through the female protagonist's perspective and of the struggles of overseas Filipino workers as domestic helpers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rappler.com/entertainment/movies/236896-hello-love-goodbye-review|title=\u2018Hello, Love, Goodbye\u2019 review: Love in a huff|last=Cruz|first=Oggs|website=Rappler|language=en|access-date=2019-08-18}}</ref> In his review, Armando B. Chavez of [[Philippine Daily Inquirer]] said that the love story stood out due to the \"backdrop of the plight of OFWs in Hong Kong.\" He also\u00a0praised the musical editing, the close-up shots of the protagonists, and performances of Bernardo and Richards, describing them as ''tour de force''. He wrote, \"This is a date movie if ever there\u2019s one. As they say back home, \u201cjust feel the feeling.\u201d Sit back, secretly dab the tears away... resistance is futile.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://usa.inquirer.net/36705/movie-review-hello-love-goodbye-rises-from-the-ordinary|title=Movie Review: \u2018Hello, Love Goodbye\u2019 rises from the ordinary|last=Chavez|first=Armando B.|date=2019-08-09|website=INQUIRER.net USA|language=en|access-date=2019-08-18}}</ref>\n\n[[Ricky Lo]] of [[The Philippine Star]] gave a generally positive review of the film particularly the comic relief provided by Abella, Bautista, and Entrata.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.philstar.com/entertainment/2019/08/15/1943362/hows-kathryn-alden|title=The \u2018hows\u2019 of Kathryn & Alden|last=Lo|first=Ricky|date=August 15, 2019|website=philstar.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=2019-08-18}}</ref> Tito Genova Valiente however disagreed and considered the trio's performances as \"aggravating\" while praising Bernardo and Richard, stating, \"There is Bernardo with perhaps the quietest performance for any actress of her generation. Bernardo can act within a small frame, holding her face solidly as if a slight movement will mar that portrayal... Alden gets the cinematographic love, as well. His Ethan starts fun and ends tragic but with lots of hope, even if it does not matter what happens to that hope. When those tears fall from Richards's eyes, they bring us back to those old, old cinemas of leading men looking beautiful and strong in grief.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://businessmirror.com.ph/2019/08/08/in-silences-hello-love-goodbye-soars/|title=In silences, \u2018Hello, Love, Goodbye\u2019 soars - Tito Genova Valiente|last=Valiente|first=Tito Genova|date=2019-08-08|website=BusinessMirror|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-18}}</ref>\n\n==Possible sequel==\nOn August 1, 2019, during the opening week of the film, lead actor Alden Richards and director Cathy Garcia-Molina expressed openness on working on a sequel for the film despite the latter's confirming plans to retire from directing to focus on her family.<ref name=sequel>{{Cite web|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/08/02/19/hello-love-goodbye-sequel-alden-direk-cathy-open-to-doing-a-follow-up-film|title='Hello, Love, Goodbye' sequel? Alden, Direk Cathy open to doing a follow-up film|last=Buan-Deveza|first=Reyma|website=ABS-CBN News|access-date=August 22, 2019|date=August 2, 2019}}</ref> On August 26, 2019, lead actress Kathryn Bernardo has also expressed similar sentiments on doing a sequel for the film.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://starcinema.abs-cbn.com/2019/8/26/news/kathryn-bernardo-open-ba-for-a-hello-love-good-51924|title=Kathryn Bernardo, open ba for a 'Hello, Love, Goodbye' sequel?|last=Is Kathryn Bernanrdo open for a 'Hello, Love, Goodbye' sequel?|website=Star Cinema|language=Tagalog, English|access-date=September 4, 2019|date=August 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Novel adaptation==\nA novel adaptation written of Hello, Love, Goodbye, authored by [[Palanca Awards|Palanca awardee]] Charmaine Lasar and published under ABS-CBN Books, was released on August 26, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rappler.com/life-and-style/books/238674-hello-love-goodbye-novel|title=\u2018Hello, Love, Goodbye\u2019 now a novel|website=Rappler|language=en|access-date=August 28, 2019|date=August 27, 2019}}</ref> The novel also include additional narration on the backstory of Joy, about her life in the Philippines prior to moving to Hong Kong and an epilogue which was not depicted in the film. Behind-the-scenes information, and on-set photos are also included in the novel.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cosmo.ph/entertainment/kathryn-bernardo-alden-richards-hello-love-goodbye-epilogue-a1320-20190828|title=You Guys, There's An Epilogue To Joy And Ethan's Story In 'Hello, Love, Goodbye'|last=Zarzuela|first=Dyan|website=Cosmopolitan|language=en-ph|access-date=August 28, 2019|date=August 28, 201}}</ref>\n\n==Television release==\nThe film premiered on television on [[Kapamilya Box Office|KBO]] from December 13\u201317, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abs-cbn.com/newsroom/listicles/2019/11/28/5-reasons-why-hello-love-goodbye-is-not-just-you?lang=en|title=5 reasons why \"Hello Love Goodbye\" is not just your typical love story|publisher=[[ABS-CBN|ABS-CBN.com]]}}</ref> It also aired again on the second week from December 20\u201325, 2019, along with the television premiere of ''[[Indak (film)|Indak]]'', and on the third week from December 27 \u2013 January 1, 2020, along with the television premiere of [[iWant]] Original Movie, ''Mga Mata sa Dilim''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertainment.abs-cbn.com/tv/updates/08110719-abs-cbn-tvplus-offers-free-kbo-movies|title=ABS-CBN TVPLUS offers free KBO movies|publisher=[[ABS-CBN|ABS-CBN.com]]}}</ref> The film premiered on [[Cinema One]] on March 15, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abs-cbn.com/newsroom/news-releases/2020/3/11/hello-love-goodbye-cinema-one-premiere?lang=en|title=Blockbuster hit \"Hello, Love, Goodbye\" debuts on Cinema One this Sunday|publisher=ABS-CBN}}</ref>\n\n== Accolades ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Award\n! scope=\"col\" | Category\n! scope=\"col\" | Recipient\n! scope=\"col\" | Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{Abbr|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n| 2019\n| [[9th AACTA Awards|AACTA Awards]]\n| Best Asian Film\n| ''Hello, Love, Goodbye''\n| {{nominated}}\n| align=\"center\"|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/10/16/19/hello-love-goodbye-up-for-top-asian-film-award-in-australia|title='Hello, Love, Goodbye' up for top Asian film award in Australia|date=October 16, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"15\" | 2020\n| rowspan=\"5\" | [[2020 Box Office Entertainment Awards|GMMSFBOE Awards]]\n| Phenomenal Box Office Star\n| Kathryn Bernardo{{hr}}Alden Richards\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"5\" align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.pep.ph/guide/movies/149220/kathryn-bernardo-alden-richards-box-office-entertainment-awards-a742-20200207|title=Kathryn Bernardo, Alden Richards, Aga Muhlach, Xia Vigor lead 51st Box Office Entertainment Awards winners|publisher=[[PEP.ph]]|language=Tagalog|last=Calderon|first=Nora|date=February 7, 2020|accessdate=February 7, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Film Actor of the Year\n| Alden Richards\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Film Actress of the Year\n| Kathryn Bernardo\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Most Popular Film Screenwriter\n| Carmi Raymundo{{hr}}Rona Go{{hr}}Cathy Garcia-Molina\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Most Popular Film Director\n| Cathy Garcia-Molina\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" | GEMS Awards\n| Best Mainstream Film\n| ''Hello, Love, Goodbye''\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"5\" align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/02/13/20/abs-cbn-stars-shows-win-big-at-the-4th-gems-hiyas-ng-sining|title=ABS-CBN stars, shows win big at the 4th GEMS Hiyas ng Sining|publisher=[[ABS-CBN|ABS-CBN News]]|language=Tagalog|date=February 13, 2020|accessdate=March 1, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Most Mainstream Film Director\n| Cathy Garcia-Molina\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Actor\n| Alden Richards\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Film Actress of the Year\n| Kathryn Bernardo\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Supporting Actor\n| Joross Gamboa\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|}\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|tt10156112|Hello, Love, Goodbye}}\n\n{{Cathy Garcia-Molina}}\n\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n[[Category:Philippine films]]\n[[Category:Star Cinema films]]\n[[Category:Films about bartenders]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Hong Kong]]\n[[Category:Films set in Hong Kong]]\n[[Category:Filipino-language films]]\n[[Category:Tagalog-language films]]\n[[Category:2010s romantic drama films]]\n[[Category:Philippine romantic drama films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Filipino romantic drama film}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Hello, Love, Goodbye\n| image          = Hello-love-goodbye-poster.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Cathy Garcia-Molina]]\n| producer       = {{ubl|[[Carlo L. Katigbak]]|[[Olivia M. Lamasan]]}}\n| screenplay     = {{Plainlist|\n* Carmi G. Raymundo\n* Rona Co\n* Cathy Garcia-Molina\n|story          = Carmi G. Raymundo\n}}\n| starring       = {{ubl|[[Kathryn Bernardo]]|[[Alden Richards]]}}\n| music          = Jessie Q. Lasaten\n| cinematography = Noel Teehankee\n| editing        = Marya Ignacio\n| studio         = [[Star Cinema]]\n| distributor    = Star Cinema\n| released       = {{Film date|2019|07|31|Philippines|2019|08|09|United States|2019|08|08|Middle East}}\n| runtime        = 118 minutes\n| country        = Philippines\n| language       = Filipino\n| gross          = {{Philippine Peso|880.6 million}} ({{USD|17.3 million}})\n}}\n\n'''''Hello, Love, Goodbye''''' is a [[List of Philippine films of 2019|2019]] Philippine [[romantic drama]] film directed by [[Cathy Garcia-Molina]] and produced by [[Star Cinema]]. The film follows Joy Fabregas ([[Kathryn Bernardo]]), a struggling [[Overseas Filipino Worker|overseas Filipino worker]], and Ethan Del Rosario ([[Alden Richards]]), a bartender, as they attempt to reconcile their personal careers and love for each other in Hong Kong. Released on July 31, 2019 in the Philippines, the film is the [[list of highest-grossing Philippine films|highest grossing Philippine film]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rappler.com/entertainment/news/238450-hello-love-goodbye-earnings-box-office-worldwide-august-23-2019|title='Hello, Love, Goodbye' makes over P800 million worldwide|last=Rappler.com|website=Rappler|language=en|access-date=2019-08-28}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://entertainment.inquirer.net/344150/hello-love-goodbye-is-highest-grossing-ph-film|title=\u2018Hello, Love, Goodbye\u2019 is highest-grossing PH film|last=Hallare|first=Katrina|website=entertainment.inquirer.net|language=en|access-date=2019-09-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/amp/news/hello-love-goodbye-sets-record-at-philippines-box-office-1238526|title=\u2018Hello, Love, Goodbye\u2019 Sets Record at Philippines Box Office|website=www.hollywoodreporter.com|access-date=2019-09-10}}</ref>\n\n== Synopsis ==\nJoy ([[Kathryn Bernardo]]) is a spunky, poor millennial who works as a domestic helper in Hong Kong. While she excels in her job and enjoys the friendship of many other empowered domestic helpers, she plans to leave the city soon.\n\nIn her journey to achieving her goals, Joy meets Filipino bartender Ethan ([[Alden Richards]]). Ethan is a sweetheart playboy already building a permanent life in Hong Kong. In a few years, he will officially become a resident in the city. After escaping responsibilities all his life, Ethan now wants to commit to a career and to his family (who also reside in Hong Kong). Joy and Ethan soon develop a friendship. The two become each other's joy against the grime and grind of Hong Kong.<ref>https://emea.kapamilya.com/events/europe/hello-love-goodbye</ref>\n\n== Cast ==\n=== Main ===\n{{multiple image\n|direction = vertical\n|align = right\n|image1 = Kathryn Bernardo at the Celebrate Mega in Iceland, 2016.jpg\n|caption1 = [[Kathryn Bernardo]] portrays Joy\n|width1 = 150\n|image2 = Alden Richards at the OMG Awards.jpg\n|caption2 = [[Alden Richards]] portrays Ethan\n|width2 = 150\n}}\n* [[Kathryn Bernardo]] as Joy Marie Fabregas: <br /> A nursing graduate who works as a domestic helper in Hong Kong.<ref name=\"scout\">{{cite news |last1=Barrientos |first1=Giselle |title=In \u2018Hello, Love, Goodbye,\u2019 an OFW gets a chance to choose herself |url=https://www.scoutmag.ph/entertainment/tv-movie/hello-love-goodbye-review-giselleb-20190802 |accessdate=September 8, 2019 |work=Scout Magazine |date=August 2, 2019}}</ref> \n* [[Alden Richards]] as Ethan Del Rosario: <br/> A womanizer bartender who is on his way of attaining [[Hong Kong residency]] status who is relatively well off compared to Fabregas.<ref name=\"scout\"/>\n\n=== Supporting ===\n* [[Maymay Entrata]] as Mary Dale Fabregas\n* [[Jameson Blake]] as Edward Del Rosario\n* [[Kakai Bautista]] as Sally Daraga\n* [[Lito Pimentel]] as Mario Del Rosario\n* [[Lovely Abella]] as Gina Marikit\n* William Lorenzo as Celso Fabregas\n* Anthony Jennings as Eric Del Rosario\n* Wilbert Ross as Joey Fabregas\n* Aliyah Billote as Liezel Fabregas\n* Angela Poliquit as Annie\n* Jon Go as Wayne\n* Poon Po Lun Lilac as Lin (Annie's mother)\n\n=== Special Participation ===\n* [[Maricel Laxa]] as Lita\n* [[Maxine Medina]] as Tanya\n* [[Jerome Ponce]] as JM\n\n==Production==\nThe film is starred by [[Kathryn Bernardo]] and [[Alden Richards]] who are affiliated with the two major rival networks in the Philippines; Bernardo with [[ABS-CBN (TV network)|ABS-CBN]] and Richards with [[GMA Network]]. The two also belongs to two different \"[[love team]]s\", Bernardo who is collectively known as Kathniel with [[Daniel Padilla]] and Richards with [[Maine Mendoza]] in [[AlDub]]. Together they play two Overseas Filipino Workers in Hong Kong who became romantically involved with each other.<ref name=gulfcrossover>{{cite news |last1=Belleza |first1=Irish Eden |title=Kathryn Bernardo and Alden Richards crossover for love |url=https://gulfnews.com/entertainment/pinoy-celebs/kathryn-bernardo-and-alden-richards-crossover-for-love-1.65625011 |accessdate=September 8, 2019 |work=Gulf News |date=August 4, 2019}}</ref> Directory Cathy Garcia-Molina said that the two main cast members were not subjected to \"baby or special treatment\" for the film project.<ref name=\"served\">{{cite news |title=Kathryn Bernardo served co-workers on \u2018Hello, Love, Goodbye\u2019 movie set in HK |url=https://filipinotimes.net/entertainment/2019/06/24/kathryn-bernardo-served-co-workers-hello-love-goodbye-movie-set-hk/ |accessdate=September 8, 2019 |work=The Filipino Times |date=June 24, 2019 |language=English, Filipino}}</ref>\n\nFilming for ''Hello, Love, Goodbye'' in Hong Kong has began by April 2019<ref>{{cite news |last1=Salonga |first1=Rita |title=Kathryn, Alden start shooting in Hong Kong |url=http://dzrhnews.com.ph/kathryn-alden-start-shooting-in-hong-kong/ |accessdate=September 8, 2019 |work=DZRH News |date=April 9, 2019}}</ref> and was completed after a month<ref>{{cite news |last1=Aguilar |first1=Krissy |title=\u2018Hello, Love, Goodbye\u2019 shoot a \u2018big adjustment\u2019 for Kathryn, Daniel |url=https://entertainment.inquirer.net/337733/hello-love-goodbye-shoot-a-big-adjustment-for-kathryn-daniel |accessdate=September 8, 2019 |work=Philippine Daily Inquirer |date=July 10, 2019}}</ref> [[Principal photography]] for the film ended by May 19, 2019 in [[Sucat]], [[Para\u00f1aque]].<ref name=\"pep1\">{{cite news |title=Kathryn Bernardo-Alden Richards movie, kakatapos lang ng principal photography |trans-title=Principal photography for Kathryn Bernardo-Alden Richards movie just finishd|url=https://www.pep.ph/pepalerts/pep-troika/143382/kathryn-bernardo-alden-richards-movie-kakatapos-lang-ng-principal-photography-a4118-20190519 |accessdate=September 8, 2019 |work=PEP.ph |publisher=Philippine Entertainment Portal, Inc. |date=May 19, 2019|language=Tagalog, English}}</ref> Post-production work for ''Hello, Love, Goodbye'' was done in Bangkok, Thailand with [[ABS-CBN Film Productions]] collaborating with Thai production firm [[Kantana Group]]. It was the first collaboration between the two firms.<ref name=\"pep2\">{{cite news |last1=Anarcon |first1=James Patrick |title=Hello Love Goodbye director on Kathryn Bernardo: \"Medyo inalila talaga namin siya sa Hong Kong.\"|trans-title=Hello Love Goodbye director on Kathryn Bernardo: \"We maltreated her a bit in Hong Kong\" |url=https://www.pep.ph/guide/movies/144103/hello-love-goodbye-director-on-kathryn-bernardo-medyo-inalila-talaga-namin-siya-sa-hong-kong-a724-20190623 |accessdate=September 8, 2019 |work=PEP.ph |publisher=Philippine Entertainment Portal, Inc. |date=June 22, 2019|language=English, Filipino}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\n===Marketing===\nA [[teaser trailer|teaser]] for ''Hello, Love, Goodbye'' was released on June 14, 2019<ref>{{cite news |title=Teaser for Kathryn Bernardo, Alden Richards movie 'Hello, Love, Goodbye' released |url=https://www.rappler.com/entertainment/movies/233086-hello-love-goodbye-teaser-trailer |accessdate=September 8, 2019 |work=Rappler |date=June 14, 2019}}</ref> while the official full trailer for  was released by Star Cinema on July 1, 2019.<ref name=posters>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cosmo.ph/entertainment/international-posters-kathryn-bernardo-alden-richards-film-hello-love-goodbye-a434-20190707|title=The International Posters For Kathryn Bernardo + Alden Richards' Film 'Hello, Love, Goodbye' Will Make You Kilig|last=Shi|first=Stephanie|date=July 7, 2019|work=Cosmopolitan|access-date=September 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Theatrical run===\n''Hello, Love, Goodbye'' premiered in the Philippines on July 31, 2019<ref name=posters/> in 465 cinemas, a record.{{Citation needed|date=September 2019}} The international screenings started on August 1, 2019.{{Citation needed|date=September 2019}} The film also made history in Saudi Arabia as the first Filipino film ever to be screened in the cinemas of Jeddah.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/08/06/19/hello-love-goodbye-is-first-ph-film-to-be-shown-in-jeddah-saudi|title='Hello, Love, Goodbye' is first PH film to be shown in Jeddah, Saudi Arabia|last=News|first=ABS-CBN|website=ABS-CBN News|access-date=2019-08-14}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Box office===\nThe film was declared the highest-grossing film of all time after earning over {{Philippine Peso|880 million}} worldwide gross revenue on September 3, 2019, replacing the film ''[[The Hows of Us]]'' that was also directed by Molina and starred by Bernardo.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/09/03/19/hello-love-goodbye-makes-history-as-highest-grossing-ph-film-of-all-time|title='Hello, Love, Goodbye' makes history as highest grossing PH film of all time|website=ABS-CBN News|access-date=2019-09-04}}</ref>\n\n====Domestic====\nThe film on its opening day earned a total of {{Philippine Peso|34.4 million}} from over 350 cinemas in the Philippines.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/08/01/19/hello-love-goodbye-earns-p34-million-on-opening-day|title='Hello, Love, Goodbye' earns P34 million on opening day|date=1 August 2019|work=ABA-CBN News|access-date=}}</ref> Three days after its local release, the film was reported to have earned {{Philippine Peso|110.8 million}}.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/08/03/19/hello-love-goodbye-collects-p110-million-in-3-days|title='Hello, Love, Goodbye' collects P110 million in 3 days|date=1 August 2019|work=ABS-CBN News|access-date=}}</ref> After four days, the film earned {{Philippine Peso|176.6 million}}<ref name=\":1\" /> and was shown in 465 cinemas nationwide.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/08/05/19/hello-love-goobye-earns-p250m-in-less-than-a-week|title='Hello, Love, Goobye' earns P250M in less than a week|date=5 August 2019|work=ABS-CBN News|access-date=}}</ref> As of August 12, 2019, the film has grossed {{Philippine Peso|505.7 million}} domestically in 13 days of showing.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://starcinema.abs-cbn.com/2019/8/12/news/hello-love-goodbye-hits-500m-in-local-box-off-51709|title=\u2018Hello, Love, Goodbye\u2019 hits \u20b1500M in local box office! {{!}} Star Cinema|last=Maglaqui|first=Rhovin|website=starcinema.abs-cbn.com|language=en|access-date=2019-08-20}}</ref> After 17 days in cinemas, the film has grossed {{Philippine Peso|603 million}} domestically.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/08/17/19/hello-love-goodbye-racks-up-p600-million|title='Hello, Love, Goodbye' racks up P600 million|publisher=ABS-CBN News|date=17 August 2019|access-date=17 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n====International====\nThe film earned {{USD|2,132,000.00}} in box office receipts abroad on its first week of release.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/08/17/19/hello-love-goodbye-racks-up-p600-million|title='Hello, Love, Goodbye' racks up P600 million|website=ABS-CBN News||date=|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=2019-08-20}}</ref> The film was also recognized now the highest-grossing Filipino film in the Middle East for earning over {{USD|1 million}} as of August 18.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abs-cbn.com/newsroom/news-releases/hello-love-goodbye-marks-box-office-record-in?lang=en|title=\"Hello, Love, Goodbye\" marks box-office record in the Middle East {{!}} ABS-CBN Corporate|website=ABS-CBN Corporation|access-date=2019-08-22}}</ref> It is also the highest-grossing Filipino film in Australia, New Zealand and United Kingdom earning over {{USD|195,336.00}},<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.the-numbers.com/movie/Hello-Love-Goodbye-(Philippines)/Australia|title=Hello, Love, Goodbye - Financial Information Australia|website=The Numbers|access-date=2019-09-10}}</ref> {{USD|60,459.00}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/intl/?page=&country=NZ&wk=2019W32&id=_fHELLOLOVEGOODB01|title=Hello, Love, Goodbye|website=www.boxofficemojo.com|access-date=2019-08-27}}</ref> and {{USD|32,313.00}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/intl/?page=&country=UK&wk=2019W32&id=_fHELLOLOVEGOODB01|title=Hello, Love, Goodbye|website=www.boxofficemojo.com|access-date=2019-09-03}}</ref> respectively.\n\n===Critical response===\nFilipino film critic Philbert Dy gave the film a rating of 4 out of 5 and praised Bernardo's performance.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://letterboxd.com/faithlessphil/film/hello-love-goodbye/|title='Hello, Love, Goodbye' Review by Philbert Dy |last=|first=|date=|work=|access-date=}}</ref> Oggs Cruz, writing for [[Rappler]], reviewed the film thus, \"Hello, Love, Goodbye' is fine entertainment \u2013 one that doesn\u2019t dumb down the issues it puts forward for the sake of a standard happy ending.\" He pointed out that while the romantic plot was formulaic and characters seemed to have become stereotypical, the film's strengths were its depiction of Hong Kong through the female protagonist's perspective and of the struggles of overseas Filipino workers as domestic helpers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rappler.com/entertainment/movies/236896-hello-love-goodbye-review|title=\u2018Hello, Love, Goodbye\u2019 review: Love in a huff|last=Cruz|first=Oggs|website=Rappler|language=en|access-date=2019-08-18}}</ref> In his review, Armando B. Chavez of [[Philippine Daily Inquirer]] said that the love story stood out due to the \"backdrop of the plight of OFWs in Hong Kong.\" He also\u00a0praised the musical editing, the close-up shots of the protagonists, and performances of Bernardo and Richards, describing them as ''tour de force''. He wrote, \"This is a date movie if ever there\u2019s one. As they say back home, \u201cjust feel the feeling.\u201d Sit back, secretly dab the tears away... resistance is futile.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://usa.inquirer.net/36705/movie-review-hello-love-goodbye-rises-from-the-ordinary|title=Movie Review: \u2018Hello, Love Goodbye\u2019 rises from the ordinary|last=Chavez|first=Armando B.|date=2019-08-09|website=INQUIRER.net USA|language=en|access-date=2019-08-18}}</ref>\n\n[[Ricky Lo]] of [[The Philippine Star]] gave a generally positive review of the film particularly the comic relief provided by Abella, Bautista, and Entrata.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.philstar.com/entertainment/2019/08/15/1943362/hows-kathryn-alden|title=The \u2018hows\u2019 of Kathryn & Alden|last=Lo|first=Ricky|date=August 15, 2019|website=philstar.com|archive-url=|archive-date=|url-status=|access-date=2019-08-18}}</ref> Tito Genova Valiente however disagreed and considered the trio's performances as \"aggravating\" while praising Bernardo and Richard, stating, \"There is Bernardo with perhaps the quietest performance for any actress of her generation. Bernardo can act within a small frame, holding her face solidly as if a slight movement will mar that portrayal... Alden gets the cinematographic love, as well. His Ethan starts fun and ends tragic but with lots of hope, even if it does not matter what happens to that hope. When those tears fall from Richards's eyes, they bring us back to those old, old cinemas of leading men looking beautiful and strong in grief.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://businessmirror.com.ph/2019/08/08/in-silences-hello-love-goodbye-soars/|title=In silences, \u2018Hello, Love, Goodbye\u2019 soars - Tito Genova Valiente|last=Valiente|first=Tito Genova|date=2019-08-08|website=BusinessMirror|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-18}}</ref>\n\n==Possible sequel==\nOn August 1, 2019, during the opening week of the film, lead actor Alden Richards and director Cathy Garcia-Molina expressed openness on working on a sequel for the film despite the latter's confirming plans to retire from directing to focus on her family.<ref name=sequel>{{Cite web|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/08/02/19/hello-love-goodbye-sequel-alden-direk-cathy-open-to-doing-a-follow-up-film|title='Hello, Love, Goodbye' sequel? Alden, Direk Cathy open to doing a follow-up film|last=Buan-Deveza|first=Reyma|website=ABS-CBN News|access-date=August 22, 2019|date=August 2, 2019}}</ref> On August 26, 2019, lead actress Kathryn Bernardo has also expressed similar sentiments on doing a sequel for the film.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://starcinema.abs-cbn.com/2019/8/26/news/kathryn-bernardo-open-ba-for-a-hello-love-good-51924|title=Kathryn Bernardo, open ba for a 'Hello, Love, Goodbye' sequel?|last=Is Kathryn Bernanrdo open for a 'Hello, Love, Goodbye' sequel?|website=Star Cinema|language=Tagalog, English|access-date=September 4, 2019|date=August 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Novel adaptation==\nA novel adaptation written of Hello, Love, Goodbye, authored by [[Palanca Awards|Palanca awardee]] Charmaine Lasar and published under ABS-CBN Books, was released on August 26, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rappler.com/life-and-style/books/238674-hello-love-goodbye-novel|title=\u2018Hello, Love, Goodbye\u2019 now a novel|website=Rappler|language=en|access-date=August 28, 2019|date=August 27, 2019}}</ref> The novel also include additional narration on the backstory of Joy, about her life in the Philippines prior to moving to Hong Kong and an epilogue which was not depicted in the film. Behind-the-scenes information, and on-set photos are also included in the novel.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cosmo.ph/entertainment/kathryn-bernardo-alden-richards-hello-love-goodbye-epilogue-a1320-20190828|title=You Guys, There's An Epilogue To Joy And Ethan's Story In 'Hello, Love, Goodbye'|last=Zarzuela|first=Dyan|website=Cosmopolitan|language=en-ph|access-date=August 28, 2019|date=August 28, 201}}</ref>\n\n==Television release==\nThe film premiered on television on [[Kapamilya Box Office|KBO]] from December 13-17, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abs-cbn.com/newsroom/listicles/2019/11/28/5-reasons-why-hello-love-goodbye-is-not-just-you?lang=en|title=5 reasons why \"Hello Love Goodbye\" is not just your typical love story|publisher=[[ABS-CBN|ABS-CBN.com]]}}</ref> It also aired again on the second week from December 20 - 25, 2019, along with the television premiere of ''[[Indak (film)|Indak]]'', and on the third week from December 27 -  January 1, 2020, along with the television premiere of [[iWant]] Original Movie, ''Mga Mata sa Dilim''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertainment.abs-cbn.com/tv/updates/08110719-abs-cbn-tvplus-offers-free-kbo-movies|title=ABS-CBN TVPLUS offers free KBO movies|publisher=[[ABS-CBN|ABS-CBN.com]]}}</ref> The film premiered on [[Cinema One]] on March 15, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abs-cbn.com/newsroom/news-releases/2020/3/11/hello-love-goodbye-cinema-one-premiere?lang=en|title=Blockbuster hit \"Hello, Love, Goodbye\" debuts on Cinema One this Sunday|publisher=ABS-CBN}}</ref>\n\n== Accolades ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Award\n! scope=\"col\" | Category\n! scope=\"col\" | Recipient\n! scope=\"col\" | Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{Abbr|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n| 2019\n| [[9th AACTA Awards|AACTA Awards]]\n| Best Asian Film\n| ''Hello, Love, Goodbye''\n| {{nominated}}\n| align=\"center\"|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/10/16/19/hello-love-goodbye-up-for-top-asian-film-award-in-australia|title='Hello, Love, Goodbye' up for top Asian film award in Australia|date=October 16, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"15\" | 2020\n| rowspan=\"5\" | [[2020 Box Office Entertainment Awards|GMMSFBOE Awards]]\n| Phenomenal Box Office Star\n| Kathryn Bernardo{{hr}}Alden Richards\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"5\" align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.pep.ph/guide/movies/149220/kathryn-bernardo-alden-richards-box-office-entertainment-awards-a742-20200207|title=Kathryn Bernardo, Alden Richards, Aga Muhlach, Xia Vigor lead 51st Box Office Entertainment Awards winners|publisher=[[PEP.ph]]|language=Tagalog|last=Calderon|first=Nora|date=February 7, 2020|accessdate=February 7, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Film Actor of the Year\n| Alden Richards\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Film Actress of the Year\n| Kathryn Bernardo\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Most Popular Film Screenwriter\n| Carmi Raymundo{{hr}}Rona Go{{hr}}Cathy Garcia-Molina\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Most Popular Film Director\n| Cathy Garcia-Molina\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" | GEMS Awards\n| Best Mainstream Film\n| ''Hello, Love, Goodbye''\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"5\" align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.abs-cbn.com/entertainment/02/13/20/abs-cbn-stars-shows-win-big-at-the-4th-gems-hiyas-ng-sining|title=ABS-CBN stars, shows win big at the 4th GEMS Hiyas ng Sining|publisher=[[ABS-CBN|ABS-CBN News]]|language=Tagalog|date=February 13, 2020|accessdate=March 1, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Most Mainstream Film Director\n| Cathy Garcia-Molina\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Actor\n| Alden Richards\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Film Actress of the Year\n| Kathryn Bernardo\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Supporting Actor\n| Joross Gamboa\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|}\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|tt10156112|Hello, Love, Goodbye}}\n\n{{Cathy Garcia-Molina}}\n\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n[[Category:Philippine films]]\n[[Category:Star Cinema films]]\n[[Category:Films about bartenders]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Hong Kong]]\n[[Category:Films set in Hong Kong]]\n[[Category:Filipino-language films]]\n[[Category:Tagalog-language films]]\n[[Category:2010s romantic drama films]]\n[[Category:Philippine romantic drama films]]\n", "name_user": "Daisynians", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hello,_Love,_Goodbye"}
{"title_page": "Heydar Babaya Salam", "text_new": "{{ITALICTITLE}}\n'''''Heydar Babaya Salam''''' ({{lang-az|Heyd\u0259r Babaya Salam}}) is an [[Azerbaijani language|Azeri]] poetical work by [[Mohammad Hossein Shahriar]], a famous [[Iranian Azerbaijani]] poet. Published in 1954 in [[Tabriz]],<ref>Brenda Shaffer. Borders and Brethren. Iran and the Challenge of Azerbaijani Identity. \u2014 MIT Press, 2002. \u2014 P. 58. \u2014 {{ISBN|9780262692779}}</ref> it is about Shahriar's childhood and his memories of his village [[Khoshgenab]] near [[Tabriz]]. ''Heydar Baba'' is the name of a mountain overlooking the village.\n\nIn ''Heydar Babaya Salam'' Shahriar narrates a nostalgia from his childhood in a village in [[Iranian Azerbaijan]].\n\nIn describing Heydar Baba, Shahryar uses the Azeri Turkish word regime toward [[Azerbaijani people|Azerbaijanis]]. Here, in every part of Azerbaijan, a Heydar Baba rises up and becomes a gigantic wall that supports and protects Azerbaijan against its foes.<ref>Hadi Sultan-Qurraie. Modern Azeri Literature. Identity, Gender and Politics in the Poetry of Moj\u0301uz. \u2014 Indiana University Ottoman and Modern Turkish Studies Publications, 2003. \u2014 P. 221. \u2014 {{ISBN|9781878318183}}</ref>\n\n==Sources==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Notes==\n*[http://www.umich.edu/~turkish/links/manuscripts/haydarbaba/haydarbaba.htm English and Turkish Translation of '''Heydar Babaya Salam''' ] (University of Michigan)\n*[http://www.umich.edu/~turkish/links/manuscripts/haydarbaba/haydarbaba.htm Audio file (mp3) of Heydar Babaya Salam ]\n*''Salam bih Haydar Baba'' and ''Salam b\u00e9 Heydar Baba'': in Azerbaijani, with [[Persian language|Persian]] translation by Bahman Fursi (1993) {{ISBN|0-9518042-7-8}} - See: [http://copac.ac.uk/ Copac library catalogue]\n*[http://shehriyat-turkce.blogspot.com/2004_03_01_shehriyat-turkce_archive.html English translation]\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EZ7z8M5KYJs \u015e\u0259hriyar - Heyd\u0259r Babaya salam-1 (audio)] {{in lang|az}}\n\n[[Category:1954 poems]]\n[[Category:Azerbaijani poetry]]\n\n\n{{poetry-stub}}\n{{Iran-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{ITALICTITLE}}\n'''''Heydar Babaya Salam''''' ({{lang-az|\u062d\u06cc\u062f\u0631\u0628\u0627\u0628\u0627\u06cc\u0647 \u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645}}) is an [[Azerbaijani language|Azeri]] poetical work by [[Mohammad Hossein Shahriar]], a famous [[Iranian Azerbaijani]] poet. Published in 1954 in [[Tabriz]],<ref>Brenda Shaffer. Borders and Brethren. Iran and the Challenge of Azerbaijani Identity. \u2014 MIT Press, 2002. \u2014 P. 58. \u2014 {{ISBN|9780262692779}}</ref> it is about Shahriar's childhood and his memories of his village [[Khoshgenab]] near [[Tabriz]]. ''Heydar Baba'' is the name of a mountain overlooking the village.\n\nIn ''Heydar Babaya Salam'' Shahriar narrates a nostalgia from his childhood in a village in [[Iranian Azerbaijan]].\n\nIn describing Heydar Baba, Shahryar uses the Azeri Turkish word regime toward [[Azerbaijani people|Azerbaijanis]]. Here, in every part of Azerbaijan, a Heydar Baba rises up and becomes a gigantic wall that supports and protects Azerbaijan against its foes.<ref>Hadi Sultan-Qurraie. Modern Azeri Literature. Identity, Gender and Politics in the Poetry of Moj\u0301uz. \u2014 Indiana University Ottoman and Modern Turkish Studies Publications, 2003. \u2014 P. 221. \u2014 {{ISBN|9781878318183}}</ref>\n\n==Sources==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Notes==\n*[http://www.umich.edu/~turkish/links/manuscripts/haydarbaba/haydarbaba.htm English and Turkish Translation of '''Heydar Babaya Salam''' ] (University of Michigan)\n*[http://www.umich.edu/~turkish/links/manuscripts/haydarbaba/haydarbaba.htm Audio file (mp3) of Heydar Babaya Salam ]\n*''Salam bih Haydar Baba'' and ''Salam b\u00e9 Heydar Baba'': in Azerbaijani, with [[Persian language|Persian]] translation by Bahman Fursi (1993) {{ISBN|0-9518042-7-8}} - See: [http://copac.ac.uk/ Copac library catalogue]\n*[http://shehriyat-turkce.blogspot.com/2004_03_01_shehriyat-turkce_archive.html English translation]\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EZ7z8M5KYJs \u015e\u0259hriyar - Heyd\u0259r Babaya salam-1 (audio)] {{in lang|az}}\n\n[[Category:1954 poems]]\n[[Category:Azerbaijani poetry]]\n\n\n{{poetry-stub}}\n{{Iran-stub}}\n", "name_user": "CuriousGolden", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fixed Azerbaijani translation", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heydar_Babaya_Salam"}
{"title_page": "Knee pad", "text_new": "{{for|the African development program|NEPAD}}\n{{unreferenced|date=June 2015}}\n[[File:Defense.gov photo essay 120707-A-8536E-269.jpg|right|thumb|US soldiers wearing knee pads]]\n[[File:Vert (sport) (181091710).jpg|thumb|Knee pads for skateboarding]]\n[[File:British Army desert fashion knee pads.jpg|thumb|British desert fashion knee pads]]\n[[File:Splav tactical knee pads.jpg|thumb|Russian military style knee pads]]\n\n'''Knee pads''' or '''kneepads''' are [[protective gear]] worn on [[knee]]s to protect them against impact [[injury]] from falling to the ground or hitting an obstacle, or to provide padding for extended [[kneeling]].\n\n==In sports==\n[[File:Polo kneepad.jpg|right|thumb|Knee pads are standard [[personal protective equipment|PPE]] for [[polo]] players]]\nKnee pads are worn in many recreational and sporting activities such as [[cycling]], [[rollerskating]], [[skateboarding]], [[cricket]], [[volleyball]], [[Team handball|handball]], [[basketball]], [[gridiron football]], [[polo]], [[dancing]], etc.  In [[polo]], knee pads serve primarily to protect the rider's knee when \"riding off\" an opponent.\n\n==In trades and military use==\nKnee pads are also used in various trades such as for the home [[handyman]], for the [[police]] [[SWAT team]]s, and they are also incorporated into [[military uniform]]s such as the [[Army Combat Uniform]] and the [[Marine Corps Combat Utility Uniform]]. These knee pads are generally designed differently{{clarify|date=June 2018}} than the general all round high impact knee pads made for sports.\n\n== In work ==\nFor example; Floor work, [[plumbing]], [[Tile|tilling]], [[mechanic]], [[climbing|climber]], bending with a constant pressure applied on knees. If work requires less or occasional kneeling, then a lighter, soft and flexible knee pad will perform better.\n\nThe knee pad should be strong enough to become the last longer companion. Another thing to take into consideration is comfort.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://topkneepads.com/best-knee-pads-for-work/#Buying_Guide:_How_To_chose_Knee_Pads_For_Work|title=Buying Guide: How To chose Knee Pads For Work|last=Alan|first=John|date=April 7, 2020|website=TopKneePads.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== For babies ==\nThe padding of the baby knee pads should be soft because the baby knee is the soft part of the body. The padding foam should be soft and ultra-durable. Knee pads should be in proper fitting according to baby knees.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://topkneepads.com/best-baby-knee-pads-for-crawling/|title=Baby Knee pads Buying Guide|last=Alan|first=John|date=April 9, 2020|website=TopKneePads.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Elbow pad]]\n*[[Gaiters]]\n*[[Poleyn]]\n*[[Shoulder pad]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{commons category|Knee pads}}\n{{Sports equipment}}\n\n[[Category:Rider apparel]]\n[[Category:Protective gear]]\n[[Category:Knee clothing|Pad]]\n\n{{clothing-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{for|the African development program|NEPAD}}\n{{unreferenced|date=June 2015}}\n[[File:Defense.gov photo essay 120707-A-8536E-269.jpg|right|thumb|US soldiers wearing knee pads]]\n[[File:Vert (sport) (181091710).jpg|thumb|Knee pads for skateboarding]]\n[[File:British Army desert fashion knee pads.jpg|thumb|British desert fashion knee pads]]\n[[File:Splav tactical knee pads.jpg|thumb|Russian military style knee pads]]\n\n'''Knee pads''' or '''kneepads''' are [[protective gear]] worn on [[knee]]s to protect them against impact [[injury]] from falling to the ground or hitting an obstacle, or to provide padding for extended [[kneeling]].\n\n==In sports==\n[[File:Polo kneepad.jpg|right|thumb|Knee pads are standard [[personal protective equipment|PPE]] for [[polo]] players]]\nKnee pads are worn in many recreational and sporting activities such as [[cycling]], [[rollerskating]], [[skateboarding]], [[cricket]], [[volleyball]], [[Team handball|handball]], [[basketball]], [[gridiron football]], [[polo]], [[dancing]], etc.  In [[polo]], knee pads serve primarily to protect the rider's knee when \"riding off\" an opponent.\n\n==In trades and military use==\nKnee pads are also used in various trades such as for the home [[handyman]], for the [[police]] [[SWAT team]]s, and they are also incorporated into [[military uniform]]s such as the [[Army Combat Uniform]] and the [[Marine Corps Combat Utility Uniform]]. These knee pads are generally designed differently{{clarify|date=June 2018}} than the general all round high impact knee pads made for sports.\n\n== In work ==\nFor example; Floor work, [[plumbing]], [[tilling]], [[mechanic]], [[climber]], bending with a constant pressure applied on knees. If work requires less or occasional kneeling, then a lighter, soft and flexible knee pad will perform better.\n\nThe knee pad should be strong enough to become the last longer companion. Another thing to take into consideration is comfort.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://topkneepads.com/best-knee-pads-for-work/#Buying_Guide:_How_To_chose_Knee_Pads_For_Work|title=Buying Guide: How To chose Knee Pads For Work|last=Alan|first=John|date=April 7, 2020|website=TopKneePads.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== For babies ==\nThe padding of the baby knee pads should be soft because the baby knee is the soft part of the body. The padding foam should be soft and ultra-durable. Knee pads should be in proper fitting according to baby knees.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://topkneepads.com/best-baby-knee-pads-for-crawling/|title=Baby Knee pads Buying Guide|last=Alan|first=John|date=April 9, 2020|website=TopKneePads.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Elbow pad]]\n*[[Gaiters]]\n*[[Poleyn]]\n*[[Shoulder pad]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{commons category|Knee pads}}\n{{Sports equipment}}\n\n[[Category:Rider apparel]]\n[[Category:Protective gear]]\n[[Category:Knee clothing|Pad]]\n\n{{clothing-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguated:tilling\u2192Tile,climber\u2192climbing", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Knee_pad"}
{"title_page": "Nile Marr", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Nile Marr\n| birth_name      = \n| image           = \n| caption         = \n| alt             = \n| image_size      = \n| landscape       = yes\n| background      = \n| years_active    = {{Start date|2006}}\u2013present\n| alias           = \n| origin          = \n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|1992|2|21|df=yes}}\n| birth_place     = [[Manchester]], England  \n| death_date      = \n| death_place     = \n| instrument      = Electric guitar<br />Acoustic guitar\n| genre           = [[Indie rock]]\n| label           = \n| associated_acts = \n| website         = \n}}\n\n'''Nile Marr''' (born 21 February 1992) is British musician and songwriter. After forming part of a trio named Man Made, he released his debut solo album ''Are You Happy Now?'' in 2020.\n\nHe is the son of fellow musician [[Johnny Marr]].\n\n==Career==\nMarr started out as a solo artist,<ref name=yp/> then as a duo with American singer-songwriter [[Meredith Sheldon]],<ref name=yp/> and then in the trio Man Made, alongside drummer Scott Griffiths and bassist Callum Rogers. They released their debut album ''TV Broke My Brain'' in 2016,<ref>[https://www.nme.com/blogs/nme-radar/man-made-interviewed-nile-marr-on-manchester-debut-albums-and-dishonesty-in-music-7303 \"Man Made Interviewed: Nile Marr On Manchester, Debut Albums And Dishonesty In Music\"] - ''[[New Musical Express|NME]]'', 14 April 2016</ref> although its constituent songs were written over a period of eight years.<ref name=yp/>\n\nMarr released a debut solo album in 2020, titled ''Are You Happy Now?''<ref name=winsford>[https://www.winsfordguardian.co.uk/leisure/leisure_events/17733882.the-heir-apparent-of-indie-royalty/ \"Nile Marr to perform at Live Bar in Warrington\"] - ''Winsford Guardian'', 27 June, 2019</ref>\n\nMarr added acoustic guitar and backing vocals on [[7 Worlds Collide]]'s 2009 album ''[[The Sun Came Out]]''.<ref name=am>[https://www.allmusic.com/artist/nile-marr-mn0001092313 Nile Marr] at AllMusic.com</ref> He has also appeared on two of his father's albums: on 2013's ''[[The Messenger (Johnny Marr album)|The Messenger]]'' he plays as a soloist, while on 2014's ''[[Playland (album)|Playland]]'' he adds backing vocals.<ref name=am/>\n\nMarr has toured extensively with German film score composer and record producer [[Hans Zimmer]].<ref name=men/>\n\nHis influences include [[John Martyn]],<ref name=yp>[https://www.yorkshirepost.co.uk/whats-on/arts-and-entertainment/music-interview-nile-marr-man-made-1802172 \"Music interview: Nile Marr of Man Made\"] - ''[[Yorkshire Post]]'', 11 March, 2016</ref> [[Fugazi]]<ref name=men/> and [[Elliott Smith]].\n\n==Discography==\n===Albums===\n;With Man Made\n*''TV Broke My Brain'' (2016)\n\n;Solo\n*''Are You Happy Now?'' (2020)\n\n===Singles===\n*\"Part Time Girl\" (from ''Are You Happy Now?''; 2019)\n\n==Personal life==\nMarr is the son of former [[The Smiths|Smiths]] guitarist and current solo artist [[Johnny Marr]] and his wife Angela.<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2009/jul/19/body-soul-johnny-marr \"My body & soul\"] - ''[[The Guardian]]'', 18 July, 2009</ref> He was named for one of his father's musical heroes, [[Chic (band)|Chic]]'s [[Nile Rodgers]].<ref name=men>[https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/whats-on/citylife-interview-nile-marr-17439276 \"CityLife interview - Nile Marr\"] - ''[[Manchester Evening News]]'', 20 December, 2019</ref> He has one sibling: a sister, Sonny.<ref name=independent>[https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/profiles/if-you-want-to-know-about-me-and-morrissey-google-it-ex-smiths-guitarist-johnny-marr-talks-8627560.html \"'If you want to know about me and Morrissey, Google it': Ex-Smiths guitarist Johnny Marr talks relationships and reunions\"] - ''[[The Independent]]'', 25 May 2013</ref>\n\nHis family moved to [[Portland, Oregon]], between 2005 and 2010.<ref name=independent/><ref>[https://www.lancashiretelegraph.co.uk/leisure/14409960.the-age-rock-star-gone-says-nile-marr-man-made-head-date-gullivers-manchester/ \"\"'The age of the rock star has gone' says Nile Marr as Man Made head for date at Gulliver's in Manchester\"] - ''[[Lancashire Telegraph]]'', 7 April 2016</ref> He returned permanently to his hometown of Manchester in 2018.<ref name=men/>\n\nHe is married to Kristen.<ref name=winsford/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.facebook.com/nilemarrofficial/ Nile Marr's official Facebook]\n*[https://twitter.com/nilemarr?lang=en Nile Marr's official Twitter]\n*[https://instagram.com/nile_marr?igshid=1ick0vzxxsj6p Nile Marr's official Instagram]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Marr, Nile}}\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:British guitarists]]\n[[Category:British songwriters]]\n[[Category:People from Manchester]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name            = Nile Marr\n| birth_name      = \n| image           = \n| caption         = \n| alt             = \n| image_size      = \n| landscape       = yes\n| background      = \n| years_active    = {{Start date|2006}}\u2013present\n| alias           = \n| origin          = \n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|1992|2|21|df=yes}}\n| birth_place     = [[Manchester]], England  \n| death_date      = \n| death_place     = \n| instrument      = Electric guitar<br />Acoustic guitar\n| genre           = [[Indie rock]]\n| label           = \n| associated_acts = \n| website         = \n}}\n\n'''Nile Marr''' (born 21 February 1992) is British musician and songwriter. After forming part of a trio named Man Made, he released his debut solo album ''Are You Happy Now?'' in 2020.\n\nHe is the son of fellow musician [[Johnny Marr]].\n\n==Career==\nMarr started out as a solo artist,<ref name=yp/> then as a duo with American singer-songwriter [[Meredith Sheldon]],<ref name=yp/> and then in the trio Man Made, alongside drummer Scott Griffiths and bassist Callum Rogers. They released their debut album ''TV Broke My Brain'' in 2016,<ref>[https://www.nme.com/blogs/nme-radar/man-made-interviewed-nile-marr-on-manchester-debut-albums-and-dishonesty-in-music-7303 \"Man Made Interviewed: Nile Marr On Manchester, Debut Albums And Dishonesty In Music\"] - ''[[New Musical Express|NME]]'', 14 April 2016</ref> although its constituent songs were written over a period of eight years.<ref name=yp/>\n\nMarr released a debut solo album in 2020, titled ''Are You Happy Now?''<ref name=winsford>[https://www.winsfordguardian.co.uk/leisure/leisure_events/17733882.the-heir-apparent-of-indie-royalty/ \"Nile Marr to perform at Live Bar in Warrington\"] - ''Winsford Guardian'', 27 June, 2019</ref>\n\nMarr added acoustic guitar and backing vocals on [[7 Worlds Collide]]'s 2009 album ''[[The Sun Came Out]]''.<ref name=am>[https://www.allmusic.com/artist/nile-marr-mn0001092313 Nile Marr] at AllMusic.com</ref> He has also appeared on two of his father's albums: on 2013's ''[[The Messenger (Johnny Marr album)|The Messenger]]'' he plays as a soloist, while on 2014's ''[[Playland (album)|Playland]]'' he adds backing vocals.<ref name=am/>\n\nMarr has toured extensively with German film score composer and record producer [[Hans Zimmer]].<ref name=men/>\n\nHis influences include [[John Martyn]],<ref name=yp>[https://www.yorkshirepost.co.uk/whats-on/arts-and-entertainment/music-interview-nile-marr-man-made-1802172 \"Music interview: Nile Marr of Man Made\"] - ''[[Yorkshire Post]]'', 11 March, 2016</ref> [[Fugazi]]<ref name=men/> and [[Elliott Smith]].\n\n==Discography==\n===Albums===\n;With Man Made\n*''TV Broke My Brain'' (2016)\n\n;Solo\n*''Are You Happy Now?'' (2020)\n\n===Singles===\n*\"Part Time Girl\" (from ''Are You Happy Now?''; 2019)\n\n==Personal life==\nMarr is the son of former [[The Smiths|Smiths]] and current solo artist [[Johnny Marr]] and his wife Angela.<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2009/jul/19/body-soul-johnny-marr \"My body & soul\"] - ''[[The Guardian]]'', 18 July, 2009</ref> He was named for one of his father's musical heroes, [[Chic (band)|Chic]]'s [[Nile Rodgers]].<ref name=men>[https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/whats-on/citylife-interview-nile-marr-17439276 \"CityLife interview - Nile Marr\"] - ''[[Manchester Evening News]]'', 20 December, 2019</ref> He has one sibling: a sister, Sonny.<ref name=independent>[https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/profiles/if-you-want-to-know-about-me-and-morrissey-google-it-ex-smiths-guitarist-johnny-marr-talks-8627560.html \"'If you want to know about me and Morrissey, Google it': Ex-Smiths guitarist Johnny Marr talks relationships and reunions\"] - ''[[The Independent]]'', 25 May 2013</ref>\n\nHis family moved to [[Portland, Oregon]], between 2005 and 2010.<ref name=independent/><ref>[https://www.lancashiretelegraph.co.uk/leisure/14409960.the-age-rock-star-gone-says-nile-marr-man-made-head-date-gullivers-manchester/ \"\"'The age of the rock star has gone' says Nile Marr as Man Made head for date at Gulliver's in Manchester\"] - ''[[Lancashire Telegraph]]'', 7 April 2016</ref> He returned permanently to his hometown of Manchester in 2018.<ref name=men/>\n\nHe is married to Kristen.<ref name=winsford/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.facebook.com/nilemarrofficial/ Nile Marr's official Facebook]\n*[https://twitter.com/nilemarr?lang=en Nile Marr's official Twitter]\n*[https://instagram.com/nile_marr?igshid=1ick0vzxxsj6p Nile Marr's official Instagram]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Marr, Nile}}\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:British guitarists]]\n[[Category:British songwriters]]\n[[Category:People from Manchester]]\n", "name_user": "Seasider53", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePersonal life", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nile_Marr"}
{"title_page": "NHL on SportsChannel America", "text_new": "{{short description|US television program}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name            = NHL on SportsChannel America\n| image                = SportsChannel.JPG\n| caption              =\n| show_name_2          = '''NHL on SportsChannel'''\n| show_name_3          =\n| genre                = Sports\n| creator              = [[SportsChannel America]]\n| writer               =\n| director             = Larry Brown<br>Billy McCoy\n| creative_director    =\n| developer            =\n| presenter            =\n| starring             = [[NHL on SportsChannel America#Announcers|See ''announcers'' section below]]\n| voices               =\n| narrated             =\n| theme_music_composer =\n| opentheme            =\n| endtheme             =\n| composer             =\n| country={{flagu|United States}}\n| language             = English\n| num_seasons          = 4\n| num_episodes         =\n| list_episodes        =\n| executive_producer   = Jeff Ruhe<ref>{{YouTube|title=Cup Finals Close 1992 SC America|id=fK3AdHkw9dw}}</ref>\n| co_exec              =\n| producer             = John Shannon\n| supervising_producer =\n| asst_producer        =\n| co-producer          =\n| editor               =\n| story_editor         =\n| location             =\n| cinematography       = Terry Ford<br>Dean Anderson<br>Bob Boykin<br>Marty Muzik\n| camera               =\n| runtime              = 180 minutes or until game ends (including commercials)\n| network              = [[SportsChannel America]]\n| picture_format       =\n| audio_format         =\n| first_run            =\n| first_aired          = {{NHL Year|1988}}\n| last_aired           = June 1, [[1991\u201392 NHL season|1992]]\n| preceded_by          =\n| followed_by          =\n| related              = ''[[Hockey Night in Canada]]'' (CBC)\n| website              =\n| production_website   =\n}}\n\n'''''NHL on SportsChannel America''''' was the presentation of [[National Hockey League]] broadcasts<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.google.com/search?q=NHL+on+SportsChannel+America&btnG=Search+Books&tbm=bks&tbo=1 |title=NHL on SportsChannel America, About 769 results (0.43 seconds) |last1= |first1= |last2= |first2= |date= |website=Google Books |publisher= |accessdate=29 April 2013}}</ref> on the now defunct [[SportsChannel|SportsChannel America]]<ref>{{YouTube|title=NHL Open SportsChannel America 1988|id=a56I5li3IpI}}</ref>[[Cable television|cable]] [[television network]].\n\n==Terms of the deal==\nTaking over for [[ESPN National Hockey Night|ESPN]]<ref>{{cite news |last=Blockus|first=Gary|date=November 16, 1988|title=MAYBE ESPN DID FANS A FAVOR IN LOSING THE NHL|url=https://www.mcall.com/news/mc-xpm-1988-11-16-2663778-story.html|work=The Morning Call|location= |access-date= }}</ref>, SportsChannel's contract paid US$51 million ($17 million<ref>{{Cite journal|url=http://cnnsi.printthis.clickability.com/pt/cpt?action=cpt&title=Scorecard+-+09.02.91+-+SI+Vault&expire=&urlID=431505592&fb=Y&url=http%3A%2F%2Fsportsillustrated.cnn.com%2Fvault%2Farticle%2Fmagazine%2FMAG1140587%2F3%2Findex.htm&partnerID=289881|title=Scorecard|date=September 2, 1991|first=Richard|last=Demak|journal=Sports Illustrated}}</ref> per year<ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://www.si.com/vault/1990/10/08/122829/the-bucks-start-here-this-off-season-the-blues-unexpectedly-made-two-players-very-rich-and-the-fallout-has-been-felt-throughout-the-league|title=The Bucks Start Here|date=October 8, 1990|first=Jay|last=Greenberg|journal=Sports Illustrated}}</ref>) over three years, more than double<ref>{{cite book |last=Bass|first=Alan|date= |title=The Great Expansion: The Ultimate Risk That Changed the Nhl Forever|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JgLqzbebH4gC&pg=PA198&dq=nhl+sportschannel+america&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjUsp3tqszgAhVD1qwKHcSGBnsQ6AEIMDAB#v=onepage&q=nhl%20sportschannel%20america&f=false|location= |publisher=iUniverse|page=198|isbn= |author-link= }}</ref> what ESPN had paid ($24 million) for the previous three years<ref>.{{Cite journal|url=http://cnnsi.printthis.clickability.com/pt/cpt?action=cpt&title=Brett+Hull+has+become+a+goal+scorer+of+near+Gretzkian+-+03.18.91+-+SI+Vault&expire=&urlID=431505807&fb=Y&url=http%3A%2F%2Fsportsillustrated.cnn.com%2Fvault%2Farticle%2Fmagazine%2FMAG1118975%2Findex.htm&partnerID=289881|title=Shooting Star|date=March 18, 1991|first=Austin|last=Murphy|journal=Sports Illustrated}}</ref> SportsChannel America managed to get a fourth NHL season for just $5 million.<ref>{{cite news |last=Joe|first=LaPointe|date=October 4, 1991|title=HOCKEY; N.H.L. Again Signs Contract With SportsChannel America|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1991/10/04/sports/hockey-nhl-again-signs-contract-with-sportschannel-america.html|work=New York Times|location= |access-date= }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|url=http://cnnsi.printthis.clickability.com/pt/cpt?action=cpt&title=Scorecard+-+02.17.92+-+SI+Vault&expire=&urlID=431505877&fb=Y&url=http%3A%2F%2Fsportsillustrated.cnn.com%2Fvault%2Farticle%2Fmagazine%2FMAG1003400%2F4%2Findex.htm&partnerID=289881|title=Scorecard|first=Richard|last=Demak|journal=Sports Illustrated|date=February 17, 1992}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Gatehouse|first=Jonathon|date= |title=The Instigator: How Gary Bettman Remade the NHL and Changed the Game Forever|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Ryb0O7riZnQC&pg=PA158&dq=nhl+sportschannel+america&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjUsp3tqszgAhVD1qwKHcSGBnsQ6AEISzAH#v=onepage&q=nhl%20sportschannel%20america&f=false|location= |publisher= Triumph Books|page=158|isbn= |author-link= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Nidetz|first=Steve|date=October 4, 1991|title=NHL FEELS PINCH IN TV DEAL|url=https://www.chicagotribune.com/news/ct-xpm-1991-10-04-9103300943-story.html|work=Chicago Tribune|location= |access-date= }}</ref>\n\nThe SportsChannel America deal was in a sense, a power play created by [[Charles Dolan]] and [[Bill Wirtz]]. Dolan was still several years away from getting control of [[Madison Square Garden]] and Wirtz owned 25% of [[SportsChannel Chicago]]. [[NHL commissioner|NHL president]] [[John Ziegler Jr.|John Ziegler]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://puckjunk.com/2018/10/29/john-ziegler-did-more-harm-than-good-for-hockey/|title=John Ziegler Did More Harm Than Good for Hockey|last=Barry|first=Sal|date=October 29, 2018|website=Puck Junk|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> convinced the [[National_Hockey_League#Organizational_structure|board of governors]] that SportsChannel America was a better alternative than a proposed NHL Channel backed by [[Paramount Pictures|Paramount]] and [[Viacom (1952\u20132006)|Viacom]] that had interests in the [[MSG Network]] and [[NESN]]. \n\n===SportsChannel's availability===\nUnfortunately, [[SportsChannel America]] was only available in a few<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hockeybuzz.com/blog/Guest-Writer/The-Good-the-Bad-and-the-Ugly-of-John-Zieglers-NHL-reign/163/95608|title=The Good, the Bad, and the Ugly of John Ziegler\u2019s NHL reign|last=Moncour|first=Gilles|date=October 29, 2018|website=HockeyBuzz.com|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> major markets (notably absent though were [[Detroit]], [[Pittsburgh]] and [[St. Louis]]<ref>{{cite news |last=Strachan|first=Al|date=March 15, 2005|title=NHL needs a TV partner|url=http://slam.canoe.com/Slam/Columnists/Strachan/2005/03/15/961494.html|work=Toronto Sun|location= |access-date= }}</ref>)<ref>{{Cite journal|url=http://cnnsi.printthis.clickability.com/pt/cpt?action=cpt&title=A+nation+wept+as+its+hero%2C+NHL+star+Wayne+Gretzky%2C+was+-+08.22.88+-+SI+Vault&expire=&urlID=431512307&fb=Y&url=http%3A%2F%2Fsportsillustrated.cnn.com%2Fvault%2Farticle%2Fmagazine%2FMAG1067639%2F4%2Findex.htm&partnerID=289881|title=Woe, Canada|date=August 22, 1988|first=E.M.|last=Swift|journal=Sports Illustrated}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=NHL broadcast boss pleased with cable move|date=May 2, 1989|first=Rudy|last=Martzke|newspaper=USA Today|page=3C}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last=Staudohar|first=Paul D.|date= |title=Playing for Dollars: Labor Relations and the Sports Business|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XLdcDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA138&lpg=PA138&dq=1990+nhl+all+star+game+on+nbc&source=bl&ots=Fg3IXbk0cY&sig=ACfU3U0aWrGJj_xOnKM27c9b3uBl42z-AQ&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjx2YKY2LXgAhURi6wKHZQIB4A4ChDoATAJegQIARAB#v=onepage&q=1990%20nhl%20all%20star%20game%20on%20nbc&f=false|location= |publisher= Cornell University Press|page=138|isbn= |author-link= }}</ref> and reached only a 1/3 of the households that [[ESPN]]<ref>{{cite news |last=Ryan|first=Bob|date=October 3, 1991|title=Underexposed NHL needs to write Dear John letter to Ziegler|url=https://www.baltimoresun.com/news/bs-xpm-1991-10-03-1991276186-story.html|work=Baltimore Sun|location= |access-date= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://puckjunk.com/2018/10/29/john-ziegler-did-more-harm-than-good-for-hockey/|title=John Ziegler Did More Harm Than Good for Hockey|last=Barry|first=Sal|date=October 29, 2018|website=Punk Junk|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> did at the time.<ref>{{cite book |title=Playing for dollars: labor relations and the sports business |last=Staudohar |first= Paul D. |authorlink= |coauthors= |year=1996 |publisher=Cornell University Press |location= |isbn= |page=137 |pages= |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Zma1OwOhQJIC&pg=PA137&dq=National+Hockey+League+on+SportsChannel+America&hl=en&ei=kDtHTe7kApP2tgP5kJDIAg&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=4&ved=0CEUQ6AEwAw#v=onepage&q=National%20Hockey%20League%20on%20SportsChannel%20America&f=false |accessdate=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://www.si.com/vault/1988/06/27/117913/a-better-open-too-much-brent-abc-improved-at-brookline-but-brent-musburgers-ego-showed-in-the-nba-finals|title=A Better Open; Too Much Brent|date=June 27, 1988|journal=Sports Illustrated|first=William|last=Taaffe}}</ref> SportsChannel America was seen in fewer than 10 million households.<ref>{{Cite journal|url=http://cnnsi.printthis.clickability.com/pt/cpt?action=cpt&title=Scorecard+-+01.16.89+-+SI+Vault&expire=&urlID=431512642&fb=Y&url=http%3A%2F%2Fsportsillustrated.cnn.com%2Fvault%2Farticle%2Fmagazine%2FMAG1126461%2F2%2Findex.htm&partnerID=289881|date=January 16, 1989|journal=Sports Illustrated|title=Scorecard}}</ref> In comparison, by the [[1991\u201392 NHL season|1991\u201392 season]], ESPN was available in 60.5 million<ref>{{cite book |last=Gatehouse|first=Jonathon|date= |title=The Instigator: How Gary Bettman Remade the NHL and Changed the Game Forever|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Ryb0O7riZnQC&pg=PA158&lpg=PA158&dq=John+Ziegler+SportsChannel+America+nhl&source=bl&ots=Ks2BELLqWL&sig=ACfU3U3Jsj9aufn4_-erSEyxo08K4BUrmA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwifvc7l4c3lAhVOd6wKHfVYDms4ChDoATAJegQICRAB#v=onepage&q=John%20Ziegler%20SportsChannel%20America%20nhl&f=false|location= |publisher= Triumph Books|page=158|isbn= |author-link=}}</ref> homes whereas SportsChannel America was available in only 25 million. As a matter of fact, in the first year of the deal ({{NHL Year|1988}}), SportsChannel America was available in only 7 million homes when compared to ESPN's reach of 50 million.<ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://www.si.com/vault/1991/10/07/125067/greed-indeed-in-its-expansion-strategy-as-in-too-many-other-matters-the-nhl-has-shown-a-passion-for-fools-gold|title=Greed, Indeed|date=October 7, 1991|first=Jay|last=Greenberg|journal=Sports Illustrated}}</ref> When the SportsChannel deal ended in [[1991\u201392 NHL season|1992]], the league returned to ESPN<ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://www.si.com/vault/1992/10/19/127337/dont-change-that-channel-contrary-to-conventional-wisdom-the-nhl-can-make-it-on-tv----with-a-few-alterations|title=Don't Change That Channel|date=October 19, 1982|first=E.M.|last=Swift|journal=Sports Illustrated}}</ref> for another contract that would pay US$80 million over five years.\n\nSportsChannel America took advantage of using their [[regional sports network]]s' feed of a game, graphics and all, instead of producing a show from the ground up, most of the time. Distribution of SportsChannel America across the country was limited to cities that had a SportsChannel regional sports network or affiliate. Very few cable systems in non-NHL territories picked it up as a stand-alone service. Regional affiliates of the [[Prime Network]] would sometimes pick up SportsChannel broadcasts, but this was often only during the playoffs, and often to justify the cost, some cable providers carrying it during the playoffs only carried it as a [[pay-per-view]] option. SportsChannel America also did not broadcast 24 hours a day at first, usually on by 6 p.m., off by 12 Midnight, then a [[Sports Plus Network|sportsticker]] for the next 18 hours.\n\n====Philadelphia====\nSince [[SportsChannel Philadelphia]] did not air until January [[1990 in television|1990]], [[PRISM (TV channel)|PRISM]] (owned by Rainbow Media, the owners of SportsChannel, at the time) picked up the [[1989 Stanley Cup Finals]]. Other than that, there was no NHL television coverage in Philadelphia except for the [[Philadelphia Flyers|Flyers]] for the first half of the original deal.\n\n{{See also|1988\u201389 Philadelphia Flyers season|1989\u201390 Philadelphia Flyers season}}\n\n===Lawsuit===\nAs previously mentioned, the NHL would return to ESPN following the [[1991\u201392 NHL season|1991\u201392 season]]. Shortly after the ESPN deal was signed, SportsChannel America would contend that its contract with the NHL gave them the right to match third-party offers for television rights for the [[1992\u201393 NHL season|1992\u201393 season]]. SportsChannel America accused the NHL of violating a nonbinding clause. SportsChannel America argued that it had been deprived of its contractual [[right of first refusal]] for the 1992\u201393 season. [[New York Supreme Court, Appellate Division|Appellate Division of New York State Supreme Court]] justice Shirley Fingerwood would deny SportsChannel America's request for an [[injunction]] against the NHL. Upholding that opinion, the [[Court of Appeals|appellate court]] found the agreement on which SportsChannel based its argument to be \"too imprecise and ambiguous\" and ruled that SportsChannel failed to show irreparable harm.\n\nIn the aftermath of losing the NHL, SportsChannel America was left with little more than outdoors shows and [[Canadian Football League]] games. For SportsChannel, the deal was a disaster overall. While the cable channel three years later, was available in 20 million homes (as previously mentioned), the broadcaster lost as much as $10 million on the agreement, and soon faded into obscurity.<ref>[http://www.njdevs.com/forums/lofiversion/index.php/t20611.html]</ref> Some local SportsChannel stations \u2013 which carried NHL games in their local markets \u2013 were not affected.\n\n==Coverage overview==\n\n===Regular season coverage===\nSportsChannel America would televise about 80\u2013100 games a season (whereas ESPN aired about 33 in the {{NHL Year|1987}} season). Whereas the previous deal with ESPN called for only one nationally televised game a week, SportsChannel America televised hockey two nights a week in NHL cities and three nights a week elsewhere.\n\nIt was very rare to have a regular-season game on SportsChannel America that wasn't a regional SportsChannel production from the [[Chicago Blackhawks]], [[Hartford Whalers]], [[New Jersey Devils]], [[New York Islanders]] or [[Philadelphia Flyers]]. The [[San Jose Sharks]] were added in {{NHL Year|1991}}. As previously suggested, SportsChannel America for the most part, used the local telecasts. The dedicated SportsChannel America station was little more than an overflow channel in the New York area for SportsChannel New York.\n\n===Special programming===\nIn [[1989 in television|1989]], SportsChannel America provided the first ever American coverage of the [[1989 NHL Entry Draft|NHL Draft]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=A look at the NHL's 27th draft|date=June 16, 1989|first=Kevin|last=Allen|newspaper=USA Today|page=8C}}</ref> In September 1989, SportsChannel America covered the [[1989\u201390 Washington Capitals season|Washington Capitals]]' training camp in Sweden and [[Season (sports)|pre-season]] tour<ref>{{Cite news|title=Soviets In, With Army and Dynamo|newspaper=Washington Post|date=December 26, 1988|first=Robert|last=Fachet}}</ref> of the Soviet Union. The Capitals were joined by the Stanley Cup champion [[Calgary Flames]], who held training camp in [[Prague, Czechoslovakia]] and then ventured to the Soviet Union. Each team played four games against [[Soviet National League]] clubs. Games were played in Moscow, [[Leningrad]], [[Kiev]] and [[Riga]]. The NHL clubs finished with a combined 6\u20132 record against the top Soviet teams, including the [[HC CSKA Moscow|Red Army]] club and [[HC Dynamo Moscow|Dynamo Moscow]]. Five of the eight contests were televised by SportsChannel America.\n\n====All-Star Game coverage====\nSportsChannel America was the exclusive American broadcaster of the [[40th National Hockey League All-Star Game|1989 All-Star Game]]. The [[41st National Hockey League All-Star Game|following year]], they covered the first ever [[NHL All-Star Game SuperSkills Competition|NHL Skills Competition]] and Heroes of Hockey game. SportsChannel America would continue their coverage of these particular events through [[43rd National Hockey League All-Star Game|1992]]. In [[1991 in American television|1991]], SportsChannel America replayed the third period of the [[42nd National Hockey League All-Star Game|All-Star Game]] on the same day that it was played. That was because [[NHL on NBC|NBC]]<ref>{{YouTube|title=1991 NHL All-Star Game, Chicago Stadium (intros, anthems)|id=tU-CXpNg5zg&t}}</ref><ref>{{YouTube|title=1991 NHL All-Star Game, Chicago Stadium (first period)|id=2LuQnlASRR0}}</ref><ref>{{YouTube|title=1991 NHL All-Star Game, Chicago Stadium (first intermission, second period)|id=qn19PhmEJYo}}</ref><ref>{{YouTube|title=1991 NHL All-Star Game, Chicago Stadium (second intermission, third period)|id=a8hfii3Xqfc&t}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1991/05/14/sports/tv-sports-stars-and-penguins-cable-compatible.html?pagewanted=print|title=TV SPORTS; Stars and Penguins: Cable Compatible|date=May 14, 1991|first=Richard|last=Sandomir|newspaper=New York Times}}</ref><ref name=1991AllStarGame>{{cite news|title=All-Star Game pinpoints NHL's limited exposure|date=January 18, 1991|first=Jack|last=Craig|newspaper=Boston Globe}}</ref> broke away from the live telecast during the third period in favor of [[Gulf War]] coverage.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n![[Play-by-play]]\n![[Color commentator|Color commentator(s)]]\n!Ice level reporters\n!Studio host\n!Studio analysts\n|-\n|[[40th National Hockey League All-Star Game|1989]]<ref>{{YouTube|title=Mark Messier Interview - 1989 All-Star game (Edmonton)|id=dYq31G53IvI}}</ref><ref>{{YouTube|title=February 7, 1989 Campbell - 9 @ Wales - 5 NHL All Star Game Sean Burke|id=t_-u7-3h2E8}}</ref><ref>{{YouTube|title=Gretzky to Kurri Goal - 1989 All-Star Game (Edmonton)|id=8qWtYNI2YQU}}</ref>\n|[[Jiggs McDonald]]\n|[[Scotty Bowman]]\n|colspan=2|[[Gary Thorne]]\n|[[Denis Potvin]] and [[Herb Brooks]]\n|}\n\n====Stanley Cup playoffs====\n=====Divisional finals=====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Teams\n![[Play-by-play]]\n![[Color commentator|Color commentator(s)]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[1989 Stanley Cup playoffs|1989]]\n|[[Bruins\u2013Canadiens rivalry|Montr\u00e9al-Boston]]\n|[[Rick Peckham]]\n|[[Gerry Cheevers]] and [[Dave Maloney]]\n|-\n|[[Flyers\u2013Penguins rivalry|Pittsburgh-Philadelphia]]\u00a0(Games 1\u20135 aired on\u00a0tape delay)\n|[[Mike Emrick]]\n|[[Bill Clement]]\n|-\n|[[Blackhawks\u2013Blues rivalry|St. Louis-Chicago]]\n|[[Pat Foley]]\n|[[Dale Tallon]]\n|-\n|[[1988\u201389 Calgary Flames season|Calgary]]-[[1988\u201389 Los Angeles Kings season|Los Angeles]]\n|[[Jiggs McDonald]]\n|[[Herb Brooks]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|