vidson (ice hockey)|John Davidson]]\n|-\n|[[1990\u201391 Edmonton Oilers season|Edmonton]]-[[1990\u201391 Minnesota North Stars season|Minnesota]]\n|[[Mike Emrick]]\n|[[Bill Clement]]\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[1992 Stanley Cup playoffs|1992]]\n|[[1991\u201392 Pittsburgh Penguins season|Pittsburgh]]-[[1991\u201392 Boston Bruins season|Boston]]\n|[[Jiggs McDonald]]\n|[[Bill Clement]]\n|-\n|[[1991\u201392 Chicago Blackhawks season|Chicago]]-[[1991\u201392 Edmonton Oilers season|Edmonton]]\n|[[Pat Foley]]\n|[[Dale Tallon]]\n|}\n\n=====Stanley Cup Finals=====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Teams\n![[Play-by-play]]\n![[Color commentator]]\n!Studio host\n!Studio analyst\n!Ice-level reporter\n|-\n|[[1989 Stanley Cup Finals|1989]]<ref>{{YouTube|title=SportsChannel America 1989 Stanley Cup Finals Game 6 Intro Theme|id=8Z_xZdtKh3E}}</ref> \n|[[1988\u201389 Calgary Flames season|Calgary]]-[[1988\u201389 Montreal Canadiens season|Montr\u00e9al]]\n|[[Jiggs McDonald]]\n|[[Bill Clement]] \n|[[Mike Emrick]]<ref>{{YouTube|title=Flames win Stanley Cup SC America 1989|id=lg9n8iO5SEA}}</ref> \n|colspan=2|[[Herb Brooks]]\n|-\n|[[1990 Stanley Cup Finals|1990]]\n|[[1989\u201390 Boston Bruins season|Boston]]-[[1989\u201390 Edmonton Oilers season|Edmonton]] \n|[[Jiggs McDonald]]\n|[[Bill Clement]] \n|[[Mike Emrick]]<ref>{{YouTube|title=1990 Stanley Cup Finals - Game 5 - Opening (Sportschannel)|id=_tdIvJKy6YQ}}</ref> \n|colspan=2|[[John Davidson (ice hockey)|John Davidson]]<ref>{{YouTube|title=Mark Messier Interview - 1990 Stanley Cup|id=OEJA0-LMqt8}}</ref> \n|-\n|[[1991 Stanley Cup Finals|1991]]\n|[[1990\u201391 Pittsburgh Penguins season|Pittsburgh]]-[[1990\u201391 Minnesota North Stars season|Minnesota]] \n|[[Jiggs McDonald]]\n|[[Bill Clement]]\n|[[Mike Emrick]]<ref>{{YouTube|title=5/25/91 - Penguins Win First Stanley Cup (3 - SportsChannel)|id=xeNDuG1qLSU}}</ref> \n|colspan=2|[[John Davidson (ice hockey)|John Davidson]] \n|-\n|[[1992 Stanley Cup Finals|1992]]\n|[[1991\u201392 Pittsburgh Penguins season|Pittsburgh]]-[[1991\u201392 Chicago Blackhawks season|Chicago]] \n|[[Jiggs McDonald]]\n|[[Bill Clement]]\n|[[Mike Emrick]]\n|colspan=2|[[John Davidson (ice hockey)|John Davidson]] \n|}\n\n==Production==\nA fair number of times in their first season, they would use their own production services for games. But very rarely would this sort of practice occur in the last three seasons. Since programming was so sparse otherwise on SportsChannel America, usually the games were replayed immediately following the live telecast.\n\nFor playoff coverage,<ref>{{Cite news|title=Schmidt tries to ease into broadcasting job|newspaper=USA Today|date=April 5, 1990|first=Michael|last=Hiestand|page=3C}}</ref> if any of the aforementioned teams made the playoffs, SportsChannel America would focus on those teams, using their facilities. For example, [[SportsChannel Chicago]]  produced the SportsChannel America coverage for the [[1989\u201390 Chicago Blackhawks season|Blackhawks]]' 1990 playoff run. Because of Hawks owner [[Bill Wirtz]]'s disdain for free and basic cable home telecasts of his games, the road games were shown in Chicago, with the home games only given short live look-ins as \"bonus coverage\". The same occurrence happened in 1992 only this time, [[1991\u201392 Chicago Blackhawks season|Blackhawks]]' home games were broadcast on a pay-per-view basis via \"[[Hawkvision]]\"<ref>{{cite news |last=Wilbon|first=Michael|date=June 1, 1992|title=FOR NHL TO GROW, ZIEGLER'S GOT TO GO|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/sports/1992/06/01/for-nhl-to-grow-zieglers-got-to-go/4cca3fce-dabf-4e86-83be-0bc08773d992/|work=Washington Post|location= |access-date= }}</ref>. Sometimes, they would use the [[Hockey Night in Canada|CBC]] feed for other series (the [[Bruins\u2013Canadiens rivalry|Boston Bruins\u2013Montreal Canadiens]] series, for example). For the [[Stanley Cup Finals|Stanley Cup Championship]], SportsChannel America would use their own facilities. They would also use their own facilities for any Conference Final series that did not involve one of SportsChannel's regional teams. SportsChannel America's [[Master control|master control]] was at a [[Cablevision]] studio in [[Oak Park, Illinois]] with its NHL studios located at [[Adelphi University]] on [[Long Island]].\n\nJohn Shannon was the senior producer of ''The NHL on SportsChannel America''.  \n\n===Announcers===\n[[Bob Papa]]<ref>{{Cite news|title=Lighter load at ABC doesn't bother McKay|date=April 12, 1990|first=Steve|last=Woodward|newspaper=USA Today|page=3C}}</ref> and Leandra Reilly were the studio hosts during the regular season coverage. For the [[Stanley Cup Finals]], [[Jiggs McDonald]]<ref>{{YouTube|title=NHL 1992 Stanley Cup Finals - Pittsburgh Penguins at Chicago Blackhawks - Game 4 Full Game|id=-vgBbF5M2zA}}</ref> served as the [[play-by-play]] man while [[Bill Clement]] was the [[color commentator]]. Also during the Stanley Cup Finals, [[Mike Emrick]]<ref>{{YouTube|title=Flames win Stanley Cup SC America 1989|id=lg9n8iO5SEA}}</ref><ref>{{YouTube|title=1990 Stanley Cup Finals - Game 5 - Opening (Sportschannel)|id=_tdIvJKy6YQ}}</ref><ref>{{YouTube|title=5/25/91 \u2013 Penguins Win First Stanley Cup (3 \u2013 SportsChannel) |id=xeNDuG1qLSU}}</ref> served as the host while [[John Davidson (ice hockey)|John Davidson]]<ref>{{cite news |last=Bradley|first=Jeff|date=May 13, 1991|title=A Strong Voice for Hockey|url=https://www.si.com/vault/1991/05/13/124200/a-strong-voice-for-hockey-john-davidson-has-become-his-sports-top-broadcaster-in-part-by-outworking-everybody-else-title%253DA|work=Sports Illustrated|location= |access-date= }}</ref> served as the rinkside<ref>{{YouTube|title=5/25/91 \u2013 Penguins Win First Stanley Cup (1 \u2013 SportsChannel)|id=OEJA0-LMqt8}}</ref><ref>{{YouTube|title=Mark Messier Interview - 1990 Stanley Cup|id=KsQ93XJHdYs}}</ref> and intermission analyst<ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://www.si.com/vault/1991/05/13/124200/a-strong-voice-for-hockey-john-davidson-has-become-his-sports-top-broadcaster-in-part-by-outworking-everybody-else|title=A Strong Voice For Hockey|date=May 13, 1991|first=Jeff|last=Bradley|journal=Sports Illustrated}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|url=http://cnnsi.printthis.clickability.com/pt/cpt?action=cpt&title=The+Penguins+staked+a+claim+to+greatness+by+winning+-+06.08.92+-+SI+Vault&expire=&urlID=411698607&fb=Y&url=http%3A%2F%2Fsportsillustrated.cnn.com%2Fvault%2Farticle%2Fmagazine%2FMAG1003855%2F2%2Findex.htm&partnerID=289881|title=Swept Away|date=June 8, 1992|first=Jon|last=Scher|journal=Sports Illustrated}}</ref> ([[Herb Brooks]] filled that role in 1989).\n\n====Play-by-play====\n*[[Mike Emrick]]\n*[[Pat Foley]]<ref>{{YouTube|title=Chicago Blackhawks at San Jose Sharks, Feb 5, 1992|id=0FTmrENQfhw}}</ref>\n*Steve Grad\n*[[John Kelly (sportscaster)|John Kelly]]\n*[[Jiggs McDonald]]\n*[[Jeff Rimer]]\n*[[Rick Peckham]]\n*[[Joe Starkey]]\n*[[Gary Thorne]]\n*[[Ken Wilson (sportscaster)|Ken Wilson]]\n\n====Color commentary====\n*[[Bruce Affleck]]\n*[[Herb Brooks]]<ref>{{Cite news|title=NBC's O'Neil known for boldness, making changes|date=May 11, 1989|first=Rachel|last=Schuster|newspaper=USA Today|page=3C}}</ref>\n*[[Gerry Cheevers]]\n*[[Bill Clement]]\n*[[John Davidson (ice hockey)|John Davidson]]\n*[[Don Edwards (ice hockey)|Don Edwards]]\n*[[John Kelly (sportscaster)|John Kelly]]\n*[[Craig Laughlin]]\n*[[Dave Maloney]]\n*[[Peter McNab]]\n*[[Joe Micheletti]]\n*[[Denis Potvin]]\n*[[Pete Stemkowski]]\n*[[Dale Tallon]]\n*[[Ed Westfall]]\n\n== Commentating crews ==\n*[[Chicago Blackhawks]]: [[Pat Foley]] and [[Dale Tallon]] (in [[1991\u201392 Chicago Blackhawks season|1992]], SportsChannel America rode them all the way through the [[1992 Stanley Cup Finals|Stanley Cup Finals]])\n**[[NBC Sports Chicago|SportsChannel Chicago]]\n*[[Hartford Whalers]]: [[Rick Peckham]] and [[Gerry Cheevers]]\n**[[NBC Sports Boston|SportsChannel New England]]\n*[[New York Islanders]]: [[Jiggs McDonald]] and [[Ed Wes